## Status Codes

### Common Status Codes

| Code | Name | Usage |
|------|------|-------|
| `200` | OK | Successful GET, PUT, PATCH |
| `201` | Created | Successful POST (creation) |
| `400` | Bad Request | Validation error, bad input |
| `401` | Unauthorized | Authentication required |
| `403` | Forbidden | Permission denied |
| `404` | Not Found | Resource not found |
| `409` | Conflict | Duplicate resource |
| `500` | Internal Server Error | Unexpected server error |
| `502` | Bad Gateway | External service error |
| `503` | Service Unavailable | Service temporarily unavailable |

### When to Use Each

```python
# 400 - Bad Request: Invalid input
if not valid_domain_format(domain):
    raise HTTPException(status_code=400, detail="Invalid domain format")

# 401 - Unauthorized: No authentication
if not current_user:
    raise HTTPException(status_code=401, detail="Authentication required")

# 403 - Forbidden: Authenticated but not authorized
if not check_program_permission(current_user, program_name, "manager"):
    raise HTTPException(status_code=403, detail="Manager access required")

# 404 - Not Found: Resource doesn't exist (or hidden for security)
# IMPORTANT: Use 404 even when access is denied to not leak resource existence
if not resource or not has_access(current_user, resource):
    raise HTTPException(status_code=404, detail="Resource not found")

# 409 - Conflict: Duplicate or conflicting data
if await repository.exists(name=request.name):
    raise HTTPException(status_code=409, detail="Resource already exists")
```

